review_blob: Had on tap at Pinnochios Beer Garden 2nd anniversary party, which this beer was brewed for. Amber/golden color with carbonation typical of the style. Aroma is of citrusy hops, very inviting. The citra and galaxy hops truly shine through in the flavor, notes of pineapple, grapefruit, and peaches. Alcohol is very well hidden. Excellent beer, hope they make it again!

This one absolutely lives up to the hype! Amazingly smooth and refined aroma and flavor. High price point makes it impossible to drink on a daily basis, but wish I could. One of the best beers I ever had in my life.
beer_name: Goose Island Bourbon County Stout - Rare

review_blob:
Ratings are for 2009 vintage (my favorite of the group) included tasting notes for all.

2007- Very chocolate tasting, however very oxidized. No real bourbon notes. A little past its prime.

2008- Heavy on chocolate, some bourbon, a little bit of oxidation. Most at tasting liked this one best.

2009- Great balance between bourbon and sweet malts, which I preferred over the heavy chocolate of 2008.

2010- Bourbon forward, cooled off significantly from when this beer is fresh. Very sweet.
Bottle shared by soonami, thanks Mike! Deep dark black color. Roast on the nose. Taste is exactly what I want from a stout, nice amounts of roast and chocolate. Great beer, wish they made more of it!
On tap. Golden in color, hops on the nose. Citrusy hops in flavor, very well balanced with malts. Great everyday beer.
Poured from a bottle. Very dark, lots of head. Roasted malts on the nose. Roast and chocolate tasting. Excellent beer, great value.

Dark brown in color, nice amount of head with some lacing. Artificial blueberries on the nose, which carries over into the flavor. Some taste of chocolate malts as well. Alcohol is well hidden, but the ariticial fruit taste harms the score for the palate.
Poured from a can. Golden in color. Basically what you should expect from the color. Very easy drinker.
Poured from a bottle. Reddish brown in color, malts dominate aroma. Nothing about this beer stands out particularly. Malty, but not in a particularly interesting way.
Poured from a bottle, 2007 vintage. Aroma was strong suit of this beer, great toffee notes. Taste however is a little on the bitter side, was hoping for a little more sweetness given the aroma.
beer_name: Schlafly Reserve Barleywine Style Ale Aged On Oak

review_blob: Poured from a bottle. Very light colored for a beer of this style. Hops dominate the aroma and taste. Very citrusy, very nice!

Poured from a bottle. Brown in color with lots of head. Maple dominates the aroma. Very sweet taste, lots of candied sugar along with the very present yams. The alcohol is well hidden, but Im glad I shared this bottle with someone else.

beer_brewer_name: Magic Hat Brewing Company (North American Breweries)
review_blob: Poured from a can. Amber in color, nice head. Apricots dominate the aroma and taste. Bitter finish. Nice beer to kick back with and relax.

Poured from a bottle. A very nice ruby color with a nice amount of champagne like head. Fruit dominates the nose. Citrus fruit in the flavor, some tartness with a dry, bitter finish. Never would put this one at almost 9%, alcohol is pretty much invisible.
Poured from a bottle. Nothing special to note on the aroma, very nice head and lacing however. Dominated by candied sugars in flavor. Hides alcohol very well. Nice beer

Poured from a bottle. Pours a nice and dark with loads of head and lacing. Bourbon on the nose, but so smooth to taste. Chocolate, licorice, and bourbon on the taste. Some nice warming heat on the way down.

Poured from a bottle, batch 4. Pours a deep crimson, some head at first, dissapates quickly, however. Very sour flavor, with some good taste from the currants. No hint at all of the 10% abv. Great sour!

On tap at Capones. Very nice and dark beer, with a bourbon aroma. Nice balance of sweetness and bourbon on the flavor. The base beer shines through nicely, and augmented nicely by the bourbon. Excellent beer!
beer_name: Dark Horse Bourbon Barrel Plead the 5th Imperial Stout

review_blob: Golden in color, nice head. Lemon with a nint of funk in the flavor. Very light on the palate, dances on the tongue.
Nice looking dark beer. Very roasted taste with a little bit of a metallic flavor. Nice beer.
Pours a nice brownish yellow. Apple and cinnamon on the nose. Carries over into the flavor. No hint of alcohol at all.
beer_name: J.K.s Cuve Winterruption Farmhouse Hard Cider

review_blob: Bottle thanks to wesnoble. Pours a bright yellow with lots of head. Cloves with a hint of funk in the flavor. Very light on the palate for the alcohol.
Black in color, hops primarily on the nose. Hoppy flavor with roasted malt flavor. No hint at all of the alcohol.
beer_name: Stone Sublimely Self Righteous Black IPA

review_blob: Poured from a bottle, deep and dark with nice head and lacing. Chocolate malts with hints of anise on the nose. Anise if in the forefront of the flavor. Great beer, especially for the price.
Poured from a bottle. Lovely citrusy hop aroma. More citrus in the flavor, with a solid malt backbone. Tasty IPA!
Pours a dark brown, aroma is of dark fruits. Dark fruits and alcohol in the taste. Nice warming sensation on the palate. Great beer!
On tap. Golden in color. Very malty in flavor with some sweetness. A slight amount of bitterness in the after taste. Good beer!
On tap. Very nice dark beer with lots of lacing. Smell is hops up front with a great malt backbone. Taste follows suit, lots of hops. Could be the first and best black IPA.
On tap. Very deep dark stout. Lots of anise on the nose, and it follows through on the taste. This one has aged nicely so far, very smooth drinker right now!
beer_name: Sierra Nevada 30th Anniversary Fritz & Kens Ale

review_blob: On tap. Nice looking red ale. Very malty on the nose and in the taste initially. Over time I started to feel the bitterness on the palate. Tastes like a malt bomb, finishes like a hop bomb. Very nice beer!
beer_name: Ballast Point Tongue Buckler Imperial Red Ale

review_blob: On tap. Excellent west coast IPA. Citrusy hops in the aroma and taste, very well done. The alcohol is pretty much invisible, could drink this all night!

beer_brewer_name: Port Brewing Co / The Lost Abbey
review_blob: 2011 vintage from a bottle. Very nice lookign beer, brownish red in color with copious head and lacing. Very floral aroma to this one. Taste is very sour up front, cherries and funk come along for the ride. The tartness lingers on the tongue. Very good beer!
On tap. Copper colored, some head with a little lacing. Not much to the aroma, though definately more flavor than other similar beers. Bitter finish. Easy beer to drink, good for a cookout.

Poured from a bottle. Pours deep black with lots of head and lacing, would be a 5 if it wasnt for some floaties. Smell is hops up front with some dark malts. The hops carry over to the flavor, as pine dominates. Some chocolate in there as well, not picking up smoke honestly.  Tasty, different take on a stout.

Poured from a bottle. Deep brown in color with some head and lacing. A few floaties too. Bourbon and coconut on the nose. Dark malts and bourbon in flavor, hints of chocolate and coconut. A slight alcohol going down, nice and warming.

Poured from a bottle. This smells and tastes like carbonated lemonade. I give it credit for hiding the alcohol well, but it would be way cheaper to make an electric lemonade, which would be about the same. Not a good beer at all.
beer_name: Hoppin Frog Turbo Shandy Citrus Ale

review_blob: Poured from a bottle. Thanks, Dan (I guess)! Smells like candy canes, tastes like candy canes. Barely any body to this one. This is not what I want from a beer at all.
beer_name: Hoppin Frog Barrel Aged Frosted Frog Christmas Ale

review_blob: 2008 vintage. Pours a dark red with lots of pink, fizzy head. Barnyard and cherries on the nose. Tart cherries dominate the flavor with some funk and oak. No hint at all of this being 8%!  So glad this was imported to Philly this year, if you see this grab it!!

Poured from a bottle. Perfect looking stout. Black with nice head and lacing. Smells of roast, cocoa powder, with a hint of cherries. Taste is primarily cocoa powder with some tartness from the cherries at the end. Nice and chewy on the palate.
beer_name: Jason Fields & Kevin Sheppard / Tregs / Stone Cherry Chocolate Stout

beer_brewer_name: Port Brewing Co / The Lost Abbey
review_blob: 2009 Brandy vintage, poured from a bottle into a glass. Dark hazy brown, completely flat of course. Lots of booze on the nose. Flavor is of chocolate, oak, and alcohol. An alcohol burn as it goes down, much better on the palate when I had this carbonated on tap. Good beer, inexcusably flat given the price point.
On tap. Golden in color. Very light drinking beer, but much more flavorful than a macro-lager. Quality session beer!
On tap. Hoppy flavor, on the piney side. Rather bitter, not very pleasant though. Below average IPA.
On tap. Nice amount of head, dissapated quickly, with no lacing however. Dark brown color. Malty flavor, very easy drinker.

beer_brewer_name: Schneider Weisse G. Schneider & Sohn GmbH
review_blob: On tap in the custom glassware. Beautiful beer, nice amount of head, with a perfectly hazy appearance. Smells of cloves, tastes of banana, cloves, with some dark maltiness. No hint of alcohol, very pleasant to drink.
Poured at a tasting into a snifter from a bottle. This beer smells and tastes like Hawaiian Tropic suntan lotion, straight up coconuts and oil.
Poured from a can into a glass. Golden in color with a nice amount of head. Nice, crisp hoppy flavor. Very drinkable, perfect beer to relax with on the deck.
Drank from a bottle. Straw golden in color, some skunk in the aroma. Bland taste with a little bit of citrus on the finish. Easy enough to drink.

Poured from a bottle into a Aecht Schlenkerla glass. Pours a nice amber color, lots of head, no lacing at all however. Smells of smoke and bbq. Smoke upfront on the taste, with a litle bit of sweetness in the finish. No alcohol on the palate, very easy drinker for 8%. Quality smoked beer!
On  tap at Monks. Pours dark with a good amount of head. Roasted malts on the nose. Typical porter taste with a slightly tart cherry finish. Very nice offering from 3F.

Poured from a bottle into a glass thanks to Soonami. Very light beer on the tongue, like all good beers of the style, but not as much flavor as some others that I had. Not sure age has been kind to it. Still a very nice beer though.
